cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.PF, cs.NI

Reasoning: 
1. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper discusses scheduling in distributed multi-server systems, which falls under the scope of this sub-category.
2. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with optimizing scheduling decisions in queueing systems, which can be considered as a control problem. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper uses stochastic ordering and sample-path tools to prove theoretical results, which are commonly used in information theory.
4. cs.PF (Performance) - The paper focuses on minimizing delay in job completion, which is a performance metric.
5. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper mentions data locality constraints, which are relevant to networking and internet architecture.
